column1: prediction
The U.S. Federal Reserve will cut the target federal funds rate by at least 25 bps at its December 2025 meeting.
p(0.7): The S&P 500 will close below 4,200 on November 29, 2025 (UTC).
Ethereum will trade above $6,000 on March 31, 2026 (UTC), using CoinDesk’s ETH closing price.
Euro area headline inflation (HICP, YoY) reported by Eurostat for December 2025 will be between 1.8% and 2.4%.
Brent crude oil front-month will settle above $100/barrel on or before January 31, 2026 (ICE settlement).
Apple will release a foldable iPhone model available for purchase by December 31, 2026.
SpaceX Starship will complete an orbital mission and successfully recover the ship intact before July 1, 2026.
The U.S. unemployment rate (BLS U-3) reported for March 2026 will be at least 5.2%.
By June 30, 2026, at least one major U.S. automaker will announce a full shutdown of an EV assembly line for 3+ months.
p(0.8): A Cat-3 or stronger hurricane will make U.S. landfall by October 31, 2025 (NHC classification).
Microsoft will report FY2026 revenue exceeding $300B in its audited 10-K.
"Dune: Part Three" will gross over $1B worldwide within 90 days of release (Box Office Mojo).
The ECB will end balance sheet reinvestments on all remaining APP/PEPP facilities by June 30, 2026.
India's real GDP growth for FY2025-26 will be reported at 6.0% or lower by the MOSPI first advance estimates.
A spot Solana ETF will be approved for listing on a major U.S. exchange by December 31, 2026.
The average 30-year fixed U.S. mortgage rate (Freddie Mac) will fall below 5.0% at least once before March 31, 2026.
An mRNA-based therapeutic (non-vaccine) will receive first FDA approval by December 31, 2026.
Bitcoin’s 30-day realized volatility (CoinDesk index) will exceed 120% at least once before May 31, 2026.
By June 30, 2026, at least one EU member state will implement a nationwide ban on selling new ICE-only passenger cars effective by 2030.
"Grand Theft Auto VI" will sell over 30 million copies in its first 60 days (publisher-reported units).
Germany will enter a technical recession (two consecutive negative QoQ real GDP) by Q1 2026 (Destatis).
Netflix will report at least 350 million global paid memberships by Q4 2026 earnings.
If the Bank of Japan exits negative rates by March 2026, USDJPY will trade below 130 within 30 days of that decision.
The average global temperature anomaly (Copernicus ERA5 monthly) for 2026 will set a new record high versus 2023.
The EU AI Act will be fully enacted with binding general-purpose AI obligations by December 31, 2026.
U.S. new housing starts (SAAR) will print below 1.1M units at least once before February 28, 2026 (Census).
OpenAI will release a model that scores ≥90% on MMLU by June 30, 2026.
Saudi Aramco will announce an upstream capacity expansion project delay of ≥12 months by year-end 2026.
By September 30, 2026, at least one U.S. state will implement a statewide ban on TikTok on government devices.
The men’s winner of Wimbledon 2026 will not be ranked in the ATP top 3 entering the tournament.
"The Legend of Zelda" next mainline release will win Game of the Year at The Game Awards the year it releases.
Eurozone unemployment will rise by at least 0.7 pp from August 2025 to any monthly print before May 31, 2026.
A U.S. federal court will enjoin enforcement of at least one major state-level social media age-verification law by June 30, 2026.
NVIDIA will report a quarterly gross margin below 70% at least once before December 31, 2026.
An OECD country will adopt a four-day workweek policy (no pay cut) across its national civil service by end-2026.
By March 31, 2026, at least one Big Tech firm will publicly commit to >$50B capex for AI infrastructure for the calendar year.
Global container shipping spot rates (Drewry WCI composite) will fall below $2,000/FEU at least once before July 31, 2026.
The 2026 FIFA World Cup winner will come from CONMEBOL.
I will lose 50 pounds by October 14, 2025.
